      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-09-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-02-03T20:07:32Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Pell Grant Restoration Act</b></p> <p> This bill restores a student's Pell Grant eligibility for any period of time during which the student qualified for, or would have qualified for, federal student loan forgiveness due to school closure, assertion of a defense against repayment, or institutional fraud or misconduct. </p> <p>Specifically, this bill provides that Pell Grants received by a student during that period of time do not count toward the student's lifetime Pell Grant eligibility period (currently 12 full-time semesters). </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
